  LINKS
To add a link in ur app u need libary "net/url", command url.Parse() and, to add it in our app, widget.NewHyperLink()

For example: 
url, _ := url.Parse("https://web.telegram.org/k/#@biberanddol1k")

link := widget.NewHyperlink("Telegram", url)

The second var is error. We can skip it or process it.

 
  IMAGES
To add a image on your web app u need to use canvas libary and command window.SetContent(container.NewGridWithColumns())
First var will be numbers of columns/rows, following will be ur images or sth

For exapmle:
image1 := canvas.NewImageFromFile("Screenshot_3.png")
label := widget.NewLabel("Image")
window.SetContent(container.NewGridWithColumns(2, image1, label))

  IMAGES FROM INTERNET
To add an image from internet we need resource. Resource - url to ur image.
url, _ := fyne.LoadResourceFromURLString("")
image := canvas.NewImageFromResource(url)

Second var is an error, we also can skip or process it. We put url as string var 

To set a dark theme in ur app we need to use settings.
myApp.Settings().SetTheme(theme.DarkTheme())

myApp  is ur var 

  APP ICON
To set a custom icon on ur app we need to set it in programm.
icon, _ := fyne.LoadResourceFromPath("icon.png")
window.SetIcon(icon)
And create exe file in terminal.
fyne package -os windows -icon icon.png

Firstly, move ur icon to root path.

